utic applications, including wound healing, anti-inflammatory, and antimicrobial properties.", "properties": [], "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Calymmodon gracilis are anti-inflammatory, antimicrobial, antioxidant, and anticancer. The anti-inflammatory property of Calymmodon gracilis makes it effective in reducing inflammation and pain, attributed to the presence of flavonoids such as quercetin and kaempferol. Additionally, the antimicrobial property of this plant is due to the presence of saponins, which have been shown to exhibit broad-spectrum antibacterial and antifungal activities, providing protection against various infections. The antioxidant property of Calymmodon gracilis is attributed to the presence of phenolic compounds such as ferulic acid, which help in scavenging free radicals and preventing oxidative stress. Furthermore, the anticancer property of this plant is due to the presence of volatile oils, particularly monoterpenes like limonene, which have been shown to exhibit anti-tumor and anti-proliferative activities.", "preparations": [{"name": "tea", "mentions": 15, "confidence_score": 137, "total_score": 2055}, {"name": "tincture", "mentions": 15, "confidence_score": 110, "total_score": 1650}, {"name": "infusion", "mentions": 14, "confidence_score": 106, "total_score": 1484}, {"name": "salve", "mentions": 15, "confidence_score": 81, "total_score": 1215}, {"name": "calymmodon decoction", "mentions": 13, "confidence_score": 72, "total_score": 936}, {"name": "calymmodon tea", "mentions": 5, "confidence_score": 48, "total_score": 240}, {"name": "calymmodon infusion", "mentions": 5, "confidence_score": 41, "total_score": 205}, {"name": "calymmodon tincture", "mentions": 5, "confidence_score": 33, "total_score": 165}, {"name": "calymmodon infused oil", "mentions": 4, "confidence_score": 22, "total_score": 88}, {"name": "suppository", "mentions": 5, "confidence_score": 17, "total_score": 85}, {"name": "calymmodon extract", "